{"TopicId":145729,"ForumId":69,"TopicTitle":"KSP crashes when returning from sleep","CreatedByName":"liquidmetalrob","CreatedById":167611,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-10T19:19:03Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"liquidmetalrob","CreatedById":167611,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-10T19:19:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m running KSP 1.1.3.1289\u00A0on Windows 10 64-bit, with no mods. The crash happens with either the 32 or 64-bit version of the game. After returning from sleep mode the game crashes.\u003Cbr\u003E\nI\u0027ve uploaded my crash report and the DxDiag file here:\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022https://drive.google.com/folderview?id=0B40rKcClN7JoZVdHX1h3V1FOeDA\u0026amp;usp=drive_web\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://drive.google.com/folderview?id=0B40rKcClN7JoZVdHX1h3V1FOeDA\u0026amp;usp=drive_web\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sal_vager","CreatedById":16426,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-10T19:40:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/167611-liquidmetalrob/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022167611\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/167611-liquidmetalrob/\u0022 id=\u0022ips_uid_2640_7\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@liquidmetalrob\u003C/a\u003E, this is a Unity3D issue and not Squads, so there\u0027s nothing Squad can do about it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut it looks like Unity has finally fixed this for version 5.3.3\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://issuetracker.unity3d.com/issues/dx9-unity-crashed-in-gfxdeviced3d9-drawbuffers-due-to-handled3ddevicelost-when-locking-windows\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EClick here for the Unity issue.\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"liquidmetalrob","CreatedById":167611,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-10T21:08:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222712338\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022145729\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221470858009\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002216426\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022sal_vager\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, sal_vager said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/167611-liquidmetalrob/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022167611\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/167611-liquidmetalrob/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@liquidmetalrob\u003C/a\u003E, this is a Unity3D issue and not Squads, so there\u0027s nothing Squad can do about it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut it looks like Unity has finally fixed this for version 5.3.3\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://issuetracker.unity3d.com/issues/dx9-unity-crashed-in-gfxdeviced3d9-drawbuffers-due-to-handled3ddevicelost-when-locking-windows\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EClick here for the Unity issue.\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/16426-sal_vager/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002216426\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/16426-sal_vager/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@sal_vager\u003C/a\u003E! Is there some way to update Unity? Or do I have to wait for Squad to incorporate the new Unity version?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-08-10T21:09:15Z\u0022 title=\u002208/10/2016 09:09  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 10, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by liquidmetalrob\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sal_vager","CreatedById":16426,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-10T21:16:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWe have to wait for the next release of KSP, as it has to be exported in the newer Unity version, and anything that breaks from the update need to be fixed too \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"liquidmetalrob","CreatedById":167611,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-11T09:46:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDo you know when the next release of KSP will be?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sal_vager","CreatedById":16426,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-11T10:44:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo, and asking for release dates is forbidden by the rules \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"liquidmetalrob","CreatedById":167611,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-11T10:50:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSorry. Thanks for all the help\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}